===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[sour]] substance.
# {{chemistry}} Any of a class of water-soluble compounds, having sour taste, that turn blue [[litmus]] red, and react with some [[metal]]s to liberate [[hydrogen]], and with [[base]]s to form [[salt]]s.
# {{chemistry}} Any compound that easily [[donate]]s [[proton]]s.
# {{chemistry}} Any compound that can [[accept]] a pair of [[electron]]s to form a [[covalent bond]].
# {{slang}} Commonly used shortened form of the [[drug]] [[Lysergic acid diethylamide]], [[Lysergic acid]] or [[LSD]].

